---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { BRAND_CONFIG } from '../../functions/brand';
---

<BaseLayout
  title={`Cookie Policy | ${BRAND_CONFIG.name}`}
  description="Information about how we use cookies on our website"
>
  <article class="legal-page">
    <section class="legal-header section-sm">
      <div class="container container-prose">
        <h1 class="legal-title">Cookie Policy</h1>
        <p class="legal-meta">Last updated: January 20, 2025</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="legal-content section">
      <div class="container container-prose">
        <div class="legal-prose">
          <h2>Introduction</h2>
          <p>
            This Cookie Policy explains how {BRAND_CONFIG.name} ("we," "us," or "our") uses cookies
            and similar technologies on our website. By using our website, you consent to our use
            of cookies in accordance with this Cookie Policy.
          </p>

          <h2>1. What Are Cookies?</h2>
          <p>
            Cookies are small text files that are placed on your device (computer, smartphone, or
            tablet) when you visit a website. Cookies are widely used to make websites work more
            efficiently and provide information to website owners.
          </p>

          <h2>2. Types of Cookies We Use</h2>

          <h3>2.1 Essential Cookies</h3>
          <p>
            These cookies are necessary for the website to function properly. They enable core
            functionality such as security, network management, and accessibility. You cannot opt
            out of these cookies without impacting how our website functions.
          </p>
          <p><strong>Examples include:</strong></p>
          <ul>
            <li>Session cookies to remember your login status</li>
            <li>Security cookies to authenticate users and prevent fraud</li>
            <li>Cookie consent preferences</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>2.2 Analytics Cookies</h3>
          <p>
            These cookies help us understand how visitors interact with our website by collecting
            and reporting information anonymously. This helps us improve our website's performance
            and user experience.
          </p>
          <p><strong>Examples include:</strong></p>
          <ul>
            <li>Google Analytics cookies to track page views and user behavior</li>
            <li>Cookies that help us understand which pages are most popular</li>
            <li>Cookies that track how long users spend on our site</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>2.3 Functionality Cookies</h3>
          <p>
            These cookies enable the website to provide enhanced functionality and personalization.
            They may be set by us or by third-party providers whose services we have added to our
            pages.
          </p>
          <p><strong>Examples include:</strong></p>
          <ul>
            <li>Cookies to remember your language preference</li>
            <li>Cookies to remember your theme preference (light/dark mode)</li>
            <li>Cookies to remember items in your shopping cart</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>2.4 Marketing Cookies</h3>
          <p>
            These cookies are used to track visitors across websites. The intention is to display
            ads that are relevant and engaging for the individual user.
          </p>
          <p><strong>Examples include:</strong></p>
          <ul>
            <li>Cookies used for targeted advertising</li>
            <li>Social media cookies to enable content sharing</li>
            <li>Cookies that track conversion rates from marketing campaigns</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>3. How We Use Cookies</h2>
          <p>We use cookies for the following purposes:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Authentication:</strong> To identify you when you visit our website and as you navigate our website</li>
            <li><strong>Personalization:</strong> To store information about your preferences and to personalize the website for you</li>
            <li><strong>Security:</strong> As an element of the security measures used to protect user accounts</li>
            <li><strong>Advertising:</strong> To help us display advertisements that are relevant to you</li>
            <li><strong>Analysis:</strong> To help us analyze the use and performance of our website</li>
            <li><strong>Cookie Consent:</strong> To store your preferences regarding the use of cookies</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>4. Third-Party Cookies</h2>
          <p>
            In addition to our own cookies, we may also use various third-party cookies to report
            usage statistics of the website and deliver advertisements on and through the website.
          </p>

          <h3>4.1 Google Analytics</h3>
          <p>
            We use Google Analytics to analyze the use of our website. Google Analytics gathers
            information about website use by means of cookies. The information gathered is used to
            create reports about the use of our website.
          </p>

          <h3>4.2 Social Media Cookies</h3>
          <p>
            Our website includes social media features, such as Facebook, Twitter, and LinkedIn
            buttons. These features may collect your IP address and which page you are visiting on
            our site, and may set a cookie to enable the feature to function properly.
          </p>

          <h2>5. Managing Cookies</h2>

          <h3>5.1 Cookie Preferences</h3>
          <p>
            You can manage your cookie preferences by clicking the "Cookie Settings" button in the
            footer of our website. This will allow you to enable or disable different categories of
            cookies.
          </p>

          <h3>5.2 Browser Settings</h3>
          <p>
            Most web browsers allow you to control cookies through their settings preferences.
            However, if you limit the ability of websites to set cookies, you may worsen your
            overall user experience, as it will no longer be personalized to you.
          </p>
          <p><strong>To manage cookies in your browser:</strong></p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Chrome:</strong> Settings → Privacy and Security → Cookies and other site data</li>
            <li><strong>Firefox:</strong> Options → Privacy & Security → Cookies and Site Data</li>
            <li><strong>Safari:</strong> Preferences → Privacy → Cookies and website data</li>
            <li><strong>Edge:</strong> Settings → Cookies and site permissions → Cookies and site data</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>5.3 Opting Out of Analytics</h3>
          <p>You can opt out of Google Analytics by installing the Google Analytics Opt-out Browser Add-on, available at:</p>
          <p><a href="https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout" target="_blank" rel="noopener">https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout</a></p>

          <h2>6. Cookie Duration</h2>
          <p>Cookies can be either session cookies or persistent cookies:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Session Cookies:</strong> These are temporary cookies that expire when you close your browser</li>
            <li><strong>Persistent Cookies:</strong> These remain on your device for a set period specified in the cookie (usually 1-2 years)</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>7. Updates to This Cookie Policy</h2>
          <p>
            We may update this Cookie Policy from time to time to reflect changes in our practices
            or for other operational, legal, or regulatory reasons. We will notify you of any
            changes by posting the new Cookie Policy on this page and updating the "Last updated"
            date.
          </p>

          <h2>8. More Information</h2>
          <p>For more information about cookies and how they work, visit:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><a href="https://www.allaboutcookies.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener">All About Cookies</a></li>
            <li><a href="https://www.youronlinechoices.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Your Online Choices</a></li>
          </ul>

          <h2>9. Contact Us</h2>
          <p>
            If you have any questions about our use of cookies, please contact us at:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Email:</strong> privacy@yourbrand.com</li>
            <li><strong>Address:</strong> [Your Business Address]</li>
            <li><strong>Phone:</strong> [Your Phone Number]</li>
          </ul>

          <div class="cookie-table">
            <h2>10. Cookies We Use</h2>
            <p>Below is a detailed list of the cookies we use on our website:</p>

            <table>
              <thead>
                <tr>
                  <th>Cookie Name</th>
                  <th>Purpose</th>
                  <th>Type</th>
                  <th>Duration</th>
                </tr>
              </thead>
              <tbody>
                <tr>
                  <td><code>cookieConsent</code></td>
                  <td>Stores your cookie consent preferences</td>
                  <td>Essential</td>
                  <td>1 year</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td><code>session_id</code></td>
                  <td>Maintains your session while browsing</td>
                  <td>Essential</td>
                  <td>Session</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td><code>_ga</code></td>
                  <td>Google Analytics - distinguishes users</td>
                  <td>Analytics</td>
                  <td>2 years</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td><code>_gid</code></td>
                  <td>Google Analytics - distinguishes users</td>
                  <td>Analytics</td>
                  <td>24 hours</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td><code>shopping_cart</code></td>
                  <td>Stores items in your shopping cart</td>
                  <td>Functionality</td>
                  <td>30 days</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td><code>theme_preference</code></td>
                  <td>Remembers your theme choice (light/dark)</td>
                  <td>Functionality</td>
                  <td>1 year</td>
                </tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>

          <div class="legal-notice">
            <p>
              <strong>Note:</strong> This is a template cookie policy. You should customize it to
              accurately reflect the cookies your website actually uses and have it reviewed by a
              legal professional to ensure compliance with applicable laws in your jurisdiction.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="legal-nav">
          <a href="/legal/privacy" class="legal-nav-link">
            Privacy Policy →
          </a>
          <a href="/legal/terms" class="legal-nav-link">
            Terms & Conditions →
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .legal-header {
    background: transparent;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
  }

  .container-prose {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .legal-title {
    font-size: var(--text-5xl);
    font-weight: var(--font-bold);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
    color: var(--color-Text-700);
  }

  .legal-meta {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    color: var(--color-Text-500);
    margin: 0;
  }

  .legal-prose {
    color: var(--color-Text-700);
    line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
  }

  .legal-prose h2 {
    font-size: var(--text-3xl);
    font-weight: var(--font-bold);
    margin-top: var(--space-3xl);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
    color: var(--color-Text-700);
  }

  .legal-prose h3 {
    font-size: var(--text-xl);
    font-weight: var(--font-bold);
    margin-top: var(--space-2xl);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
    color: var(--color-Text-700);
  }

  .legal-prose p {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
    font-size: var(--text-base);
  }

  .legal-prose ul,
  .legal-prose ol {
    margin: var(--space-lg) 0;
    padding-left: var(--space-2xl);
  }

  .legal-prose li {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .legal-prose a {
    color: var(--color-Primary-500);
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  .legal-prose a:hover {
    color: var(--color-Primary-600);
  }

  .legal-prose code {
    background: var(--color-Neutral-100);
    padding: 2px 6px;
    border-radius: 3px;
    font-family: 'Courier New', monospace;
    font-size: 0.9em;
  }

  /* Cookie Table */
  .cookie-table {
    margin-top: var(--space-3xl);
    overflow-x: auto;
  }

  .cookie-table table {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    margin-top: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .cookie-table th,
  .cookie-table td {
    padding: var(--space-md);
    text-align: left;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-Neutral-200);
  }

  .cookie-table th {
    background: var(--color-Background-100);
    font-weight: var(--font-semibold);
    color: var(--color-Text-700);
  }

  .cookie-table td {
    color: var(--color-Text-500);
  }

  .cookie-table tr:hover td {
    background: var(--color-Neutral-50);
  }

  .legal-notice {
    margin-top: var(--space-3xl);
    padding: var(--space-xl);
    background: var(--color-Warning-50);
    border-left: 4px solid var(--color-Warning);
    border-radius: var(--border-radius-md);
  }

  .legal-notice p {
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--color-Warning-700);
  }

  .legal-nav {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-md);
    margin-top: var(--space-3xl);
    padding-top: var(--space-2xl);
    border-top: 2px solid var(--color-Neutral-200);
  }

  .legal-nav-link {
    padding: var(--space-lg);
    background: var(--color-Background-100);
    border-radius: var(--border-radius-md);
    font-weight: var(--font-semibold);
    color: var(--color-Text-700);
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: all var(--transition-fast);
  }

  .legal-nav-link:hover {
    background: var(--color-Primary-500);
    color: white;
    transform: translateX(5px);
  }

  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .legal-title {
      font-size: var(--text-6xl);
    }

    .legal-nav {
      flex-direction: row;
    }
  }
</style>
